## Getting Started

### Prerequisites

- Node.js 18+ and npm
- Git
- Deno (for Edge Function development)

### Quick Start

```bash
# 1. Clone the Repository
git clone https://github.com/ekexintelligence/ekex-core.git
cd ekex-core

# 2. Configure Environment
cp .env.example .env.local
# Edit .env.local -- NEVER commit this file

# 3. Install Dependencies
npm install

# 4. Start Development Server
npm run dev
```

### Access Points

| Service | URL |
|---|---|
| Frontend Dev | http://localhost:5173 |
| Admin Dashboard | http://localhost:5173/admin |

### Build for Production

```bash
npm run build
```

Entry: `src/main.jsx` -> `src/App.jsx` (router) -> pages/

---

## Edge Functions

All 20 backend functions are deployed as Deno serverless handlers.

### Function Pattern

```javascript
import { createClientFromRequest } from 'npm:@base44/sdk@0.8.25';

Deno.serve(async (req) => {
  const base44 = createClientFromRequest(req);
  const user = await base44.auth.me();
  if (!user) return Response.json({ error: 'Unauthorized' }, { status: 401 });
  // ... logic
});
```

### Environment Variables

| Variable | Required | Used In |
|---|---|---|
| COMMAND_CENTER_URL | Yes | notifyCommandCenter, flagSupplierMisconduct, deliverReport |
| RESEND_API_KEY | Yes | sendMatchEmail |

> Never commit secrets. All variables are set via platform dashboard -> Settings -> Environment Variables.

